<subSubSection box="[199,1034,438,465]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,1034,438,465]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,438,464]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Distribution.</emphasis>
From northern 
<collectingCountry box="[529,615,439,465]" name="Mexico" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[751,862,439,465]" name="Argentina" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Maps 17–18).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,474,500]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Piza, 1981)" baseAuthorityName="Piza" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[344,648,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventer" status="n. syn.">
<emphasis box="[344,500,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. nigriventer</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Piza Jr., S. T." box="[517,640,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="215 - 218" refId="ref42473" refString="Piza Jr., S. T. (1981) Mais duas especies novas de Dysonia do Brasil (Orth., Tettigoniidae, Phaneropterinae). Revista de Agricultura, Piracicaba, 56 (4), 215 - 218." type="journal article" year="1981">Piza, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[657,736,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[657,736,475,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">n. syn.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, is proposed as a synonym under 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puntifrons">
<emphasis box="[1130,1275,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. puntifrons</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref38497" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1878) Monographie der Phaneropteriden, F. A. Brockhaus, Wien, 401 pp., pls. 1 - 8." type="book chapter" year="1878">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1878</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. When comparing the structure of the male terminalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[1049,1097,511,537]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
specimens of both species no differences are found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[199,462,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pirani">
<emphasis box="[199,462,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Lichenomorphus pirani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Costa Lima, A. M. &amp; Guitton, N." box="[476,796,583,609]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="69 - 89" refId="ref40314" refString="Costa Lima, A. M. &amp; Guitton, N. (1961) Genero Dysonia (Orth. Tettig. Phaneropteridae) Parte II Conclusao. Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 33, 69 - 89." type="journal article" year="1961">
<collectingRegion box="[476,542,583,609]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Costa</collectingRegion>
<collectingRegion box="[547,606,583,609]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Lima</collectingRegion>
&amp; Guitton, 1961
</bibRefCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,911,583,609]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">n. comb.</emphasis>
, originally assigned to genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1862" box="[1241,1334,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Dysonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1241,1334,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Dysonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" box="[257,445,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[257,445,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Lichenomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it agrees much better with the diagnostic characters of this genus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Braun &amp; García" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1248,1347,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pirani">
<emphasis box="[1248,1347,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. pirani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the peculiarity of having the outer branch of the male cerci noticeably elongated and flattened.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,1421,691,717]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
A key to species is provided below (
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 2012" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2012" box="[606,917,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinyaevi">
<emphasis box="[606,727,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. sinyaevi</emphasis>
Gorochov, 2012
</taxonomicName>
, only known from a female, is not included).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1057,1456,1480]" box="[151,1057,1456,1480]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1456,1480]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Map 18.</emphasis>
Distribution map of 
<taxonomicName box="[452,702,1456,1480]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[452,622,1456,1480]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Lichenomorphus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in Southeast 
<collectingCountry box="[839,901,1456,1480]" name="Brazil" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[949,1053,1456,1480]" name="Argentina" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="61" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,573,1562,1589]" box="[151,573,1562,1589]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,573,1562,1589]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" box="[366,573,1562,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[366,573,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Lichenomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<key lastPageId="61" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyStep pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
1. Frons predominantly black; male cerci hook-shaped, apex sclerotized, usually the outer branch curved inward, almost over the inner branch, with some exceptions like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2012" box="[657,743,1661,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oscari">
<emphasis box="[657,743,1661,1682]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. oscari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; male subgenital plate is mostly flattened, flexible, and longer than the cerci............................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" box="[151,1436,1719,1741]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1719,1741]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">- Frons predominantly white or very light brown; male subgenital plate and cerci variable in shape...................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" box="[151,1436,1749,1771]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1749,1771]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">2. Outer branch of the male cerci curved inward, almost over inner branch.......................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" box="[151,1436,1778,1800]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1778,1800]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
- Branches of the male cerci similar in size and curved to opposite sides (divergent) (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1114,1778,1800]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,197,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@62.[159,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 34. Lichenomorphus species. Cerci and subgenital plates. A, D, E. L. montealegrezi. Habitus in lateral view, cerci and subgenital plates. B–C. L. oscari. F–G. L. berezini. H–I. L. ocraceithorax. J–K. L. fuscifrons. (Figs. H–K. after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 34B</figureCitation>
)..... 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 2012" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2012" box="[1189,1436,1778,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oscari">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1189,1276,1778,1799]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. oscari</emphasis>
Gorochov, 2012
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" box="[151,1436,1807,1829]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1807,1829]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">3. Styli of the male subgenital plate conspicuous and well-developed.............................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" box="[151,1436,1836,1859]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1836,1859]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
- Styli of the male subgenital plate absent (
<figureCitation box="[623,710,1837,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,197,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@62.[159,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 34. Lichenomorphus species. Cerci and subgenital plates. A, D, E. L. montealegrezi. Habitus in lateral view, cerci and subgenital plates. B–C. L. oscari. F–G. L. berezini. H–I. L. ocraceithorax. J–K. L. fuscifrons. (Figs. H–K. after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 34E</figureCitation>
).......................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castaneda, 2011" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda" authorityYear="2011" box="[1027,1436,1836,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montealegrezi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1027,1193,1836,1858]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. montealegrezi</emphasis>
Cadena-Castañeda, 2011
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead pageId="60" pageNumber="61">4. Face mostly black or brown like the rest of the ventral surface of the body; styli of male subgenital plate conical and mediumsized............................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
- Face except clypeus and labrum white, the rest of the lower margin of the body black; styli of male subgenital plate cylindrical and elongated (
<figureCitation box="[373,463,1954,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,197,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@62.[159,1429,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 34. Lichenomorphus species. Cerci and subgenital plates. A, D, E. L. montealegrezi. Habitus in lateral view, cerci and subgenital plates. B–C. L. oscari. F–G. L. berezini. H–I. L. ocraceithorax. J–K. L. fuscifrons. (Figs. H–K. after Costa-Lima &amp; Guitton, 1961)." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 34G</figureCitation>
)......................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 2012" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2012" box="[1170,1436,1954,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Lichenomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berezini">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1170,1276,1954,1976]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. berezini</emphasis>
Gorochov, 2012
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="61" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1631,2035]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<keyLead pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
